1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:11,333
<i> From now on,</i>

2
00:00:11,467 --> 00:00:13,333
<i>don't meddle with my strategy,
all right?</i>

3
00:00:13,467 --> 00:00:15,433
<i>Or do you want to
go up against me?</i>

4
00:00:15,567 --> 00:00:16,733
<i> Is Glen really the reason</i>

5
00:00:16,867 --> 00:00:18,367
<i> you're in such a bad mood?</i>

6
00:00:18,500 --> 00:00:21,100
<i> He stole my role in the movie,</i>

7
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,833
<i>and we'll kill
each other first...</i>

8
00:00:22,967 --> 00:00:25,200
<i>before he takes my current
position too.</i>

9
00:00:25,333 --> 00:00:26,733
<i> Son of a duck.</i>

10
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:29,867
<i>Oh, so what did your
investigation come up with?</i>

11
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:31,900
<i>It's the same group
that hit both the museum</i>

12
00:00:32,033 --> 00:00:33,633
<i> and the San Isidro Rural Bank.</i>

13
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:35,600
<i>Do you think
he's telling the truth?</i>

14
00:00:38,433 --> 00:00:40,267
<i>That's enough! We're the police!</i>

15
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,367
<i> Stay out of this!</i>

16
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:43,200
<i> Lieutenant Conde?</i>

17
00:01:10,700 --> 00:01:12,400
Roman...

18
00:01:12,867 --> 00:01:14,867
How's the task I gave you?

19
00:01:19,667 --> 00:01:21,133
It's all good, Boss.

20
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,367
It's all set.

21
00:01:24,067 --> 00:01:25,500
Good.

22
00:01:30,033 --> 00:01:31,700
Oh...

23
00:01:38,333 --> 00:01:39,600
What? Huh?

24
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:42,067
I said back off or I'll shoot!

25
00:01:45,767 --> 00:01:48,467
I told you to stay out of this!

26
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,033
Freeze!

27
00:02:11,267 --> 00:02:13,333
Put your hands up!

28
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:21,767
Don't do something you'll
regret, Lieutenant Conde.

29
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:23,300
You don't understand, Sergeant.

30
00:02:23,433 --> 00:02:24,867
I'm on the job here!

31
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:27,600
The Chief said you haven't
even reported for duty yet!

32
00:02:27,733 --> 00:02:29,233
You don't believe me?

33
00:02:29,367 --> 00:02:30,933
Let's go to the station
and talk to the Chief!

34
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:32,500
I'm really going
to bring you in!

35
00:02:32,633 --> 00:02:34,633
You can explain everything at
the precinct!

36
00:02:37,400 --> 00:02:39,200
Sergeant...

37
00:02:41,667 --> 00:02:43,767
We don't have to do this.

38
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:46,367
Put that down!

39
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,267
- You've gone too far!
- Lieutenant Conde!

40
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:56,867
That's enough!

41
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,000
I'm placing you under arrest!

42
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,733
There. I've got no weapon now.

43
00:03:08,867 --> 00:03:10,800
You can't arrest me anymore.

44
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:13,500
Noble, cuff him.

45
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:18,967
I said...

46
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:46,733
I saw your clash
with the Mayor earlier.

47
00:03:46,867 --> 00:03:47,767
That was awesome.

48
00:03:47,900 --> 00:03:49,633
So intense.

49
00:03:49,767 --> 00:03:52,000
It felt like I was watching one
of your old movies.

50
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:55,700
That Joaquin
still doesn't see that...

51
00:03:55,867 --> 00:03:59,700
in this story, I'm the star.

52
00:04:01,167 --> 00:04:02,667
Just a reminder...

53
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,067
Mayor's got a strong machine
behind him.

54
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:06,967
We'll match that.

55
00:04:07,100 --> 00:04:09,167
How's our budget doing,
by the way?

56
00:04:09,300 --> 00:04:10,300
We're good, Boss.

57
00:04:10,433 --> 00:04:12,467
It's literally in the bag

58
00:04:14,633 --> 00:04:15,900
Good!

59
00:04:16,033 --> 00:04:16,933
Add some more.

60
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:17,967
Of course.

61
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,267
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

62
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:26,833
To your takeover.

63
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,500
- So, Abdul?
- What?

64
00:04:32,633 --> 00:04:35,000
Are you happy that we're now
village patrol?

65
00:04:35,533 --> 00:04:37,900
Well, kinda of, I mean,
I'm enjoying it.

66
00:04:38,033 --> 00:04:40,100
But, Mar, of course,
it's even better

67
00:04:40,233 --> 00:04:42,600
now that we live with captain.

68
00:04:42,733 --> 00:04:43,767
Right.

69
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:47,600
You better be thankful my house
upstairs was available.

70
00:04:47,733 --> 00:04:49,867
But, Captain,
look what time it is,

71
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:51,467
and still no action.

72
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:52,700
That's right, Captain.

73
00:04:52,833 --> 00:04:53,900
Our batons are going to waste.

74
00:04:54,033 --> 00:04:55,400
We won't be able to use it.

75
00:04:55,533 --> 00:04:57,500
Yes, I wish something would
happen

76
00:04:57,633 --> 00:04:59,167
so we can use these...

77
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,833
"Something-something"?

78
00:05:02,600 --> 00:05:04,733
Hey! Cut it out!

79
00:05:04,867 --> 00:05:05,933
What are you even doing?

80
00:05:06,067 --> 00:05:08,867
It's better that there's no
action...

81
00:05:09,000 --> 00:05:11,267
because election
is just around the corner.

82
00:05:11,400 --> 00:05:13,967
We need to stay calm.

83
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:16,267
-You're the one being too eager.
- Captain! Captain!

84
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:18,100
There's trouble over there!

85
00:05:18,233 --> 00:05:19,267
- Trouble?
- Yes!

86
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:20,267
Hey, there's trouble!

87
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,467
- There's trouble!
- Let's go!

88
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:22,733
- Go check on them!
- Oh, go!

89
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:25,200
- Let's go! Who is that?
- I'll come with you..

90
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:28,833
Chief, we've covered
a lot in the investigation.

91
00:05:29,067 --> 00:05:30,433
At this point,
I'm practically related

92
00:05:30,567 --> 00:05:32,067
to the employees there.

93
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:33,633
One of them even asked me
to be a godfather,

94
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,800
from how many times
I've asked around.

95
00:05:36,367 --> 00:05:39,700
Yes a lot,
but it's going nowhere!

96
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:42,867
Chief, we're sorry.

97
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,867
It's been a slow one.

98
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:48,267
Every lead we get
ends up a dead end.

99
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:52,033
It can't always be like this,
Lieutenant Robles.

100
00:05:52,167 --> 00:05:53,333
It's easy for you...

101
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:55,467
you're not the one being
pressured by the mayor.

102
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:56,967
I am!

103
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:00,800
So don't waste too much time
chasing dead leads!

104
00:06:00,933 --> 00:06:02,433
If they go nowhere,

105
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:03,600
drop them!

106
00:06:03,733 --> 00:06:05,067
Don't worry,

107
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,900
we'll look for
a different angle.

108
00:06:09,133 --> 00:06:11,933
Chief, sorry, but you need to
step outside

109
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:15,267
- Oh, hello!
- Mayor Joaquin! Mayor Joaquin!

110
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,833
Oh?

111
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:19,733
Wow, look at that,
your security is so lax.

112
00:06:19,867 --> 00:06:20,767
See this?

113
00:06:20,900 --> 00:06:23,900
I were a hitman,
I'd have taken you out just now!

114
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,633
You're slick, Mira.

115
00:06:26,767 --> 00:06:27,900
Just doing my job, Mayor.

116
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:29,933
How can I help you?

117
00:06:30,067 --> 00:06:32,267
I just want to ask
what you think

118
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:35,033
about your former partymates

119
00:06:35,167 --> 00:06:36,767
who switched sides

120
00:06:36,900 --> 00:06:40,033
to Mr. Victor Santiago's party?

121
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,467
Let's sit down.

122
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:44,367
Oh, boy.

123
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:46,600
You know,
they're free to choose.

124
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:48,333
It's their own choice.

125
00:06:48,467 --> 00:06:50,733
They'll only realize later

126
00:06:50,867 --> 00:06:54,733
that they picked the wrong side.

127
00:06:54,867 --> 00:06:59,067
So does that mean they made the
wrong choice?

128
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,833
Of course.

129
00:07:00,967 --> 00:07:02,233
You know how it is...

130
00:07:02,367 --> 00:07:06,500
people know who's got
the heart and the pull.

131
00:07:07,300 --> 00:07:11,533
But what about
the village you used to control?

132
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:14,467
Now that some of your councilors
have switched parties,

133
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:18,500
how will that affect
the coming election?

134
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:21,033
Mira, that's all for now.

135
00:07:21,533 --> 00:07:23,167
Thank you so much.

136
00:07:23,767 --> 00:07:24,433
I have to go.

137
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,333
Thank you.

138
00:07:33,067 --> 00:07:34,867
Captain, they're here!

139
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:35,967
Hey, wait a minute.

140
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,167
What's this commotion?

141
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,600
Hey, hey, hey.

142
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:39,833
You know what?

143
00:07:39,967 --> 00:07:41,500
Let's settle this peacefully,
all right?

144
00:07:41,633 --> 00:07:43,100
Don't fight anymore.

145
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,733
Captain, how are we
supposed to fix this?

146
00:07:45,867 --> 00:07:48,300
Nena wants to vote for Amo.

147
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:51,400
But I told her she should vote
for the Mayor.

148
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:54,700
Wow! And you think you know
politics?

149
00:07:54,833 --> 00:07:57,200
You only want to vote
for the Mayor

150
00:07:57,333 --> 00:07:58,867
because he is your favorite
actor!

151
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,167
- Right? Right?
- Amo, is also an actor.

152
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:01,467
- Back in the day, why?
- Oh, come on!

153
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,900
If you're going
to argue like this,

154
00:08:03,033 --> 00:08:03,833
it'll never end!

155
00:08:03,967 --> 00:08:04,800
Hey!

156
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:06,100
Listen up, all of you.

157
00:08:06,233 --> 00:08:08,667
How about you do
community service?

158
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,533
- Change your...
- Oh, answer.

159
00:08:10,667 --> 00:08:13,533
What? I just passed by
a mountain of garbage.

160
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:14,967
You want that?

161
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:16,800
Oh...

162
00:08:16,933 --> 00:08:17,733
Never mind, Captain.

163
00:08:17,867 --> 00:08:18,567
We have reconciled.

164
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:19,833
We made up, Captain.

165
00:08:19,967 --> 00:08:21,267
Oh, you did?

166
00:08:21,433 --> 00:08:22,867
Well, don't let it
happen again, okay?

167
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:25,700
No more fighting,
no more trouble, got it?

168
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:26,867
All right, Captain.

169
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:27,933
- Okay.
- Thank you,

170
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:29,767
- we'll head out first.
- No more arguments.

171
00:08:30,900 --> 00:08:32,667
Go to bed already, okay?

172
00:08:32,800 --> 00:08:33,700
Oh my...

173
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:35,633
That's what the fight
was all about? Politics.

174
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:37,533
- Just politics.
- All right, let's go.

175
00:08:37,667 --> 00:08:38,700
Let's go, team.

176
00:08:38,833 --> 00:08:40,633
Special menu tonight.

177
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:42,600
- Lumpia again?
- It's evening.

178
00:08:42,733 --> 00:08:45,033
What's good is the lumpia and...

179
00:08:45,167 --> 00:08:46,933
If you want, this one's yours.

180
00:08:47,733 --> 00:08:49,300
If you want,
I'll forgive you for the durian.

181
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:51,333
If I...

182
00:08:52,233 --> 00:08:54,067
Robles, help me out.

183
00:08:56,433 --> 00:08:58,267
Chief, this looks bad.

184
00:09:00,433 --> 00:09:02,600
Oh my, oh my, oh my...

185
00:09:02,733 --> 00:09:04,233
Oh...

186
00:09:04,867 --> 00:09:07,200
Wow, that's some nasty blows.

187
00:09:08,333 --> 00:09:10,133
He was beaten to a pulp.

188
00:09:10,533 --> 00:09:12,600
How many people
did they fight with?

189
00:09:13,067 --> 00:09:14,100
Just one, Sir.

190
00:09:14,233 --> 00:09:15,500
What?

191
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:18,067
Sergeant, what happened?

192
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,467
Lieutenant Conde, Sir.

193
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,700
Wait, Sir Tonyo?

194
00:09:25,667 --> 00:09:27,833
Sir Tonyo! Sir Tonyo!

195
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,000
My God!

196
00:09:29,133 --> 00:09:30,133
Sir Tonyo, are you all right?

197
00:09:30,267 --> 00:09:32,233
- Sir Tonyo!
- Abi...

198
00:09:32,367 --> 00:09:33,733
Let's do that later.

199
00:09:33,867 --> 00:09:35,300
Come on.

200
00:09:38,700 --> 00:09:40,567
Take care of Conde.

201
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:43,167
All right, Chief.

202
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,533
Joaquin, let's finalize
the details

203
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:52,933
for your parade tomorrow, okay?

204
00:09:53,433 --> 00:09:55,700
So here's what we're going to
do, Mayor.

205
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:58,900
First thing tomorrow,
we head to San Martin.

206
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:00,433
Why San Martin?

207
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,533
That's based on the itinerary
you approved.

208
00:10:03,667 --> 00:10:06,467
We've already informed
the village.

209
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:07,967
A village...

210
00:10:08,100 --> 00:10:09,700
Can you leave us for a moment?

211
00:10:10,733 --> 00:10:12,300
Excuse me.

212
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:17,100
Joaquin, what's the problem?

213
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,900
Your plan's all wrong.

214
00:10:19,033 --> 00:10:20,533
We need to prioritize
the villages

215
00:10:20,667 --> 00:10:22,267
that turned against me.

216
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:24,067
That's not possible.

217
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:27,067
It took them days to finalize

218
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,067
the parade logistics.

219
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:31,233
What's the problem, Joaquin?

220
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:33,967
Why the sudden change of heart?

221
00:10:35,567 --> 00:10:36,833
Daddy!

222
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:38,200
Hi, Dear.

223
00:10:38,333 --> 00:10:40,133
Hello!

224
00:10:40,267 --> 00:10:41,500
Hi, Mommy.

225
00:10:41,633 --> 00:10:43,200
Mommy!

226
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,333
Daddy, what's with the
long face?

227
00:10:50,467 --> 00:10:52,167
I'm just stressed, Dear.

228
00:10:53,433 --> 00:10:56,333
Sophia, could you...

229
00:10:56,867 --> 00:10:58,733
get me some water?

230
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,133
Okay.

231
00:11:01,667 --> 00:11:03,233
Mommy.

232
00:11:06,133 --> 00:11:08,000
- Oh, Dear? Oh?
- Daddy...

233
00:11:08,167 --> 00:11:11,367
Didn't I promise I'd help you
with the campaign?

234
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,600
So, what can I be of service?

235
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:18,300
Dear, I'm really hungry
right now.

236
00:11:18,433 --> 00:11:19,600
Can we eat first?

237
00:11:19,733 --> 00:11:20,900
We'll talk later.

238
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:21,933
Okay.

239
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:25,733
Daddy, I'm really craving
for Japanese food.

240
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:28,933
Captain, who are you voting
for as mayor?

241
00:11:30,033 --> 00:11:32,667
Of course, whoever
my granddaughter likes...

242
00:11:32,800 --> 00:11:35,567
Victor “Amo” Santiago.

243
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:36,767
Oh, see?

244
00:11:36,900 --> 00:11:38,767
Captain and I agree!

245
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:41,067
Well, this guy Mar,

246
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:44,833
is with Joaquin Guerrero's
party.

247
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:48,767
Of course, let's stick with
someone tried and tested.

248
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:50,600
Or maybe you just
don't like El Hepe

249
00:11:50,733 --> 00:11:53,633
because he didn't accept you
into his party?

250
00:11:53,767 --> 00:11:56,067
Hey, excuse me.

251
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:57,500
He offered,

252
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,400
I turned him down.

253
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:01,833
Besides, I don't like
that El Hepe guy.

254
00:12:01,967 --> 00:12:02,733
Wait.

255
00:12:02,867 --> 00:12:04,767
Why not, Captain?

256
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:06,567
- You are such a gossipmonger.
- Oh.

257
00:12:07,433 --> 00:12:10,267
Captain, another thing...

258
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:11,467
between him and me,

259
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:14,433
who do you think suits
Bobby more?

260
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:15,900
- Oh...
- That's me!

261
00:12:16,033 --> 00:12:17,067
Good question. I like that!

262
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,167
That's me!

263
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:19,167
Neither.

264
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:21,300
What?

265
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:22,733
Why not, Captain?

266
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:23,933
Oh my, you should...

267
00:12:24,067 --> 00:12:26,400
you should stop pretending.

268
00:12:28,067 --> 00:12:30,533
I know what you're both hiding.

269
00:12:31,200 --> 00:12:35,233
These days, people should be
coming out already.

270
00:12:38,367 --> 00:12:40,900
Captain, please!
Let's just keep it between us,

271
00:12:41,033 --> 00:12:41,800
okay? It's a secret!

272
00:12:41,933 --> 00:12:43,400
And, Capatain...

273
00:12:43,533 --> 00:12:45,200
we did this before in the
province

274
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:47,933
But, it didn't work.

275
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:49,667
Why is it not working?

276
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:54,300
Captain, we only get partners
when we pretend to be guys.

277
00:12:54,433 --> 00:12:57,767
So please, Captain,
let's keep it our secret.

278
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:00,800
- Let's keep it our secret.
- Yes.

279
00:13:00,933 --> 00:13:03,467
Fine, but leave my granddaughter
out of it.

280
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:06,367
Thank you, fairy godmother!

281
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:08,167
Thank you!

282
00:13:08,300 --> 00:13:09,700
Oh, amazing, right?

283
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:10,833
Grandmother!

284
00:13:10,967 --> 00:13:11,900
- Oh, it's Bobby.
- It's Bobby.

285
00:13:12,033 --> 00:13:14,567
Captain, there might be
crimes there?

286
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:17,500
- Bobby, good evening.
- Good evening.

287
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:19,333
Want me to walk you home?

288
00:13:19,467 --> 00:13:20,633
Huh? This is my house already.

289
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:21,833
Oh, is it?

290
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,133
Okay, we'll continue
our patrol then.

291
00:13:24,267 --> 00:13:26,267
- Captain, Bobby.
- Good night, good night.

292
00:13:26,400 --> 00:13:27,367
- Good night.
- Bobby!

293
00:13:27,500 --> 00:13:28,500
- Take care, okay?
- Good night.

294
00:13:28,633 --> 00:13:29,933
Good night.

295
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:31,967
What happened with those two?

296
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:38,000
Lieutenant Conde and I met,
Grandmother.

297
00:13:38,867 --> 00:13:40,367
Really?

298
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:42,533
What happened?

299
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:46,467
I'm sorry,

300
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:48,333
plans changed
because of the Mayor.

301
00:13:48,467 --> 00:13:49,333
But don't worry...

302
00:13:49,467 --> 00:13:50,900
if you're staying up,

303
00:13:51,033 --> 00:13:52,733
I'll stay with you.

304
00:13:53,267 --> 00:13:55,800
You don't have to do that,
Councilor.

305
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:57,867
Even just coffee's fine.

306
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,233
Coffee? I'll throw
in doughnuts too.

307
00:14:00,367 --> 00:14:01,867
Partner it with doughnuts.

308
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:03,367
You're the best, Boss.

309
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:05,900
You should be running
for vice mayor already.

310
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:09,733
Next time, next time.

311
00:14:09,867 --> 00:14:10,933
Okay, I'll leave you now.

312
00:14:11,067 --> 00:14:12,733
- Thank you.
- Okay, okay, okay.

313
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:19,000
So how do you feel about that,
Dear?

314
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:24,733
I'm just trying to be patient,
Mom.

315
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,600
If dad says...

316
00:14:28,100 --> 00:14:30,033
I'm not ready to be vice mayor
yet, I'll follow.

317
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,300
So, be it.

318
00:14:31,433 --> 00:14:32,567
I'll just follow that.

319
00:14:32,700 --> 00:14:34,467
Oh, well...

320
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:37,233
Patience is a virtue

321
00:14:37,367 --> 00:14:39,233
when playing this game, Dear.

322
00:14:39,367 --> 00:14:41,133
Just remember that.

323
00:14:41,767 --> 00:14:43,733
In thought and in action, Mom.

324
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:45,367
If you only knew.

325
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:49,000
Well, I'm just making sure.

326
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:51,533
Because I know how eager you are

327
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:54,167
to be your dad's running mate.

328
00:14:56,667 --> 00:15:00,400
Maybe he's waiting for Faye to
be his running mate?

329
00:15:00,533 --> 00:15:03,567
Well, are you threatened?

330
00:15:04,033 --> 00:15:05,433
Well...

331
00:15:05,567 --> 00:15:07,633
Faye wants to be a celebrity.

332
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:11,633
Even if Dad wants her
in politics,

333
00:15:11,767 --> 00:15:14,033
I know he'll still support what
she really wants.

334
00:15:14,167 --> 00:15:16,567
That's why I'm just trying
to play my cards right.

335
00:15:17,267 --> 00:15:22,433
I know I'm the only true heir
when it comes to politics.

336
00:15:35,433 --> 00:15:38,700
That Lieutenant Conde is crazy.

337
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:40,333
He's just creating a mess,

338
00:15:40,467 --> 00:15:42,233
bothering my granddaughter.

339
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,033
It's okay, Grandmother.

340
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:47,133
That's how cops are
always on duty.

341
00:15:47,267 --> 00:15:48,233
Oh, then what?

342
00:15:48,367 --> 00:15:50,567
Were you able to talk to
Lieutenant Conde?

343
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:51,933
Not yet.

344
00:15:52,067 --> 00:15:54,200
He's still at the precinct,
locked up.

345
00:15:54,767 --> 00:15:57,067
Well, you did beat him up.

346
00:15:57,200 --> 00:16:00,067
Take it easy next time.

347
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:02,633
I actually felt bad for him,
Grandmother.

348
00:16:03,100 --> 00:16:05,233
I really pity him, Grandmother.

349
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:07,700
I hope Chief approves it.

350
00:16:07,833 --> 00:16:10,667
I know he's itching to get back
to police work.

351
00:16:10,833 --> 00:16:12,333
He's probably desperate

352
00:16:12,467 --> 00:16:15,467
to find out who's behind

353
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,200
the San Isidro bank robbery.

354
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,633
Careful, okay?

355
00:16:19,767 --> 00:16:22,967
Your new boss might
get annoyed with you.

356
00:16:23,100 --> 00:16:24,600
You're still new.

357
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:27,033
Oh, food!

358
00:16:27,167 --> 00:16:28,300
Wow!

359
00:16:28,433 --> 00:16:29,367
Eating time.

360
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,300
That's ours!

361
00:16:30,433 --> 00:16:31,800
Share some please, Captain!

362
00:16:31,933 --> 00:16:33,067
No.

363
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,933
Just grab a plate!

364
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:38,500
What's this, chicken?

365
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:41,300
Captain, next time, beef please!

366
00:16:41,467 --> 00:16:43,333
- Here.
- Hurry up, Abdul.

367
00:16:43,467 --> 00:16:44,867
Let's eat!

368
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:45,900
There.

369
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:47,333
- Captain!
- Sit here, sit here.

370
00:16:47,467 --> 00:16:48,433
Bobby, good evening.

371
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:49,800
We're eating already, okay?

372
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:52,033
All right. All right.

373
00:16:52,167 --> 00:16:53,733
Captain, next time we want beef.

374
00:16:53,867 --> 00:16:54,833
That's right.

375
00:16:54,967 --> 00:16:55,800
Chicken?

376
00:16:55,933 --> 00:16:57,367
Isn't that for my granddaughter?

377
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:59,033
Yes.

378
00:16:59,167 --> 00:16:59,833
Let them be, Grandmother.

379
00:16:59,967 --> 00:17:01,000
Okay, we'll just eat.

380
00:17:01,133 --> 00:17:02,700
All right, here...
have some eggs.

381
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:03,733
So good!

382
00:17:03,867 --> 00:17:05,967
- This is delicious.
- You smelled it too.

383
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,467
Wake up.

384
00:17:18,233 --> 00:17:20,600
Do you realize you're sleeping
in my spot?

385
00:17:20,733 --> 00:17:22,067
What?

386
00:17:23,067 --> 00:17:25,800
I don't even know
how I got here.

387
00:17:25,933 --> 00:17:27,800
And I'm a cop!

388
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:29,233
You're a cop?

389
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:31,100
- You're a cop?
- Oh, so you're a cop?

390
00:17:31,233 --> 00:17:32,300
I knew it.

391
00:17:32,433 --> 00:17:34,433
I knew your face
looked familiar.

392
00:17:35,133 --> 00:17:37,733
Aren't you the same cop who
arrested us last month?

393
00:17:38,300 --> 00:17:39,633
You're going to pay for that
now.

394
00:17:42,667 --> 00:17:44,733
I don't want any trouble, okay!

395
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,733
Oh? He says he doesn't want
trouble.

396
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,400
- Sir...
- Cut it out, all of you!

397
00:17:49,533 --> 00:17:50,700
Sir...

398
00:17:51,867 --> 00:17:53,167
Bok, sorry about this, okay?

399
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:55,033
I just had them mess with you to
see

400
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:57,600
if you're still tough.

401
00:17:57,733 --> 00:17:58,833
Don't be scared.

402
00:17:58,967 --> 00:18:01,200
The guys here? Their only cases
are stealing<i> aratilis</i> .

403
00:18:02,333 --> 00:18:05,167
Bok, get me out of here.

404
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:06,967
No problem, of course.

405
00:18:07,100 --> 00:18:08,800
That's why I came here.

406
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:17,033
Get out of there.

407
00:18:17,433 --> 00:18:19,033
Scared.

408
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,633
Sir, don't forget your
promise to us, okay?

409
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:22,900
Boss, food.

410
00:18:23,033 --> 00:18:24,433
Let's talk about that later.

411
00:18:24,567 --> 00:18:27,233
I already made a promise,
and I have keep it.

412
00:18:28,633 --> 00:18:29,900
How are you?

413
00:18:31,033 --> 00:18:35,500
Bok, you kinda smell like the
back of a watch now, huh.

414
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:40,967
You sure you're still fit
for service?

415
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:43,167
Maybe you're getting rusty.

416
00:18:44,567 --> 00:18:46,933
Conde, Chief wants to see you.

417
00:18:47,067 --> 00:18:49,667
- There it is.
- Okay, good luck.

418
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,267
- Noble!
- Ma'am?

419
00:19:04,100 --> 00:19:05,533
I was just thinking...

420
00:19:06,633 --> 00:19:08,033
Isn't it a little hard to
believe that Amo

421
00:19:08,167 --> 00:19:11,067
didn't know his masks were
stolen from the museum?

422
00:19:11,200 --> 00:19:13,733
Ma'am, sounds like you're
dreaming about Amo already.

423
00:19:13,867 --> 00:19:15,133
It's not like that.

424
00:19:15,267 --> 00:19:17,900
But that's just the natural
progression of the case.

425
00:19:18,967 --> 00:19:21,400
First, the masks were stolen.

426
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:23,200
Then, those same masks were used

427
00:19:23,333 --> 00:19:25,333
in the bank robbery.

428
00:19:25,467 --> 00:19:26,833
So what am I supposed to think?

429
00:19:26,967 --> 00:19:30,200
Okay, let's say
he is connected to it.

430
00:19:30,933 --> 00:19:32,433
But why would he steal?

431
00:19:32,567 --> 00:19:33,800
Isn't he rich?

432
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:35,367
He's even a famous actor.

433
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:37,000
And he's running
for office, right?

434
00:19:37,133 --> 00:19:38,200
Exactly.

435
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:40,767
Which means, he'll need
a bigger campaign budget.

436
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:42,467
That's true,

437
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,933
they do spend a lot on that.

438
00:19:45,067 --> 00:19:47,100
And once they're elected, that's
when they pay themselves back.

439
00:19:47,233 --> 00:19:48,433
I need to talk to Chief.

440
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:49,300
Let's go!

441
00:19:50,033 --> 00:19:51,367
Oh...

442
00:19:52,167 --> 00:19:53,767
Okay, Ma'am.

443
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,733
Let's go, let's go.

444
00:20:04,967 --> 00:20:06,333
Get in.

445
00:20:11,467 --> 00:20:12,700
Sir...

446
00:20:17,667 --> 00:20:19,100
Robles?

447
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,300
All right, go ahead.

448
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:27,000
Sir.

449
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:43,400
Sit down.

450
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,100
You've been jailed
four times, Conde,

451
00:20:50,233 --> 00:20:51,300
ever since you got suspended.

452
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:52,733
Sir...

453
00:20:52,867 --> 00:20:54,400
This is different, Sir.

454
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:56,967
Please, just hear me out.

455
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:01,233
All right, explain.

456
00:21:02,600 --> 00:21:06,533
I'm following a lead on the
San Isidro bank robbery.

457
00:21:08,733 --> 00:21:10,300
Is that you're investigating

458
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:14,500
the San Isidro bank robbery?
